  <recipe id="Press a bag crispy cookies">
    <head>
      <title>Press a bag crispy cookies</title>
      <source>Mdm June Chiang Yi Ling</source>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Cookies</cat>
				<cat class="diet">Nut-free</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description><xhtml:p>I found this to be a simple cookie to make all year round.</xhtml:p>

<xhtml:p>My 9 year old son, Wong Loong Wai, loves making this when he has some free time.</xhtml:p></description>
    <ingredients system="metric">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>340</qty>
            <unit>g</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>butter</item>
		  <ing-note> (cool salted cubes) </ing-note>
<!--340g butter (cool salted cubes)-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>200</qty>
            <unit>g</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>sugar</item>
<!--200g sugar (white)-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>280</qty>
            <unit>g</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>flour</item>
<!--280g plain flour-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>200</qty>
            <unit>g</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>corn starch</item>
<!--200g corn flour-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vanilla essence</item>
<!--2 tsp vanilla essence-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
          </amt>
          <item>egg</item>
<!--1 middle-size egg-->
        </ing>
        <ing optional="yes">
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>emplex</item>
		  <ing-note> makes the cookies taste crisp and last longer </ing-note>
<!--2 tsp emplex (optional) make cookies taste crisp and last long-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>Do not grease baking tray. Perheat oven before start <temp><qty>180</qty><tempunit unit="C" system="metric">degrees</tempunit><!--180  C--></temp></step>
      <step>Steps:- a) butter, sugar, emplex, essence into mixer and beat at middle speed</step>
      <step>b) add beaten egg bit by bit into mixer</step>
      <step>c) add flour bit by bit into mixer (slow speed)</step>
      <note>Scrape sides of mixer and beat a little more (creaming method)</note>
      <step>d) scoop into pipping bag and pipe into a heart shape if possible.</step>
      <step>or straight line or whatever you fancy.</step>
      <step>e) bake at <temp><qty>180</qty><tempunit unit="C" system="metric">degrees</tempunit><!--180 C--></temp> for 20 mins.</step>
      <step>Happy trying - Juneze</step>
      <note>I did a web search for Emplex. It is an emulsifier, specifically sodium stearoyl lactylate, and is made by American Ingredients Company. It is used to give cookies extra crunch. --SJ</note>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
